[2026-03-11T21:17:32Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BPmWkiCP2StYpJuZzrB4mc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document with all the file paths and key findings:\n\n## Summary: Web UI Project Detail Page - Prompt File Accordion Code\n\nI've found all the code responsible for the Web UI project detail page's accordion dropdowns for prompt files. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### Key Files and Components:\n\n**1. Frontend Template (HTML + JavaScript)**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**2. Backend Handler**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### Code Flow:\n\n#### Frontend (Template - Lines 53-94):\n\n1. **API Call to Load Prompt Files** (lines 44-76)\n   - JavaScript function `loadProjectInfo()` fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info`\n   - Receives JSON with `prompt_files` array containing:\n     - `path`: file path (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/implement.md`)\n     - `history`: array of commit entries with `sha`, `date`, `message`\n   - Renders `<details>` accordions for each prompt file\n   - Lists each commit history entry as clickable items (lines 59-65)\n\n2. **Display File Contents on Click** (lines 78-94)\n   - Function `toggleDiff(el)` handles accordion item clicks\n   - Currently fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file={file}&sha={sha}`\n   - Displays result in a `<pre>` block labeled `diff-block`\n\n#### Backend (Handler - Lines 978-1095):\n\n**Handler Registration** (Line 136):\n```\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff\", h.handleAPIPromptDiff)\n```\n\n**1. `handleAPIProjectInfo()` (Lines 978-1064)**\n   - Loads prompt files from `.cloche/prompts/` directory\n   - Runs `git log --follow --format=%H %aI %s` for each file (line 1028)\n   - Extracts: SHA, date, and commit message\n   - Returns JSON with `prompt_files` array to frontend\n\n**2. `handleAPIPromptDiff()` (Lines 1066-1095)**\n   - **ISSUE**: Named \"PromptDiff\" but this is where file contents are displayed\n   - Receives `file` and `sha` query parameters\n   - Runs `git diff sha^..sha -- file` (line 1086)\n   - Returns the git diff output as text/plain\n\n### Potential Issue Location:\n\nThe problem appears to be in the **endpoint behavior**:\n- The endpoint is called `prompt-diff` but in the UX it displays what should be the **file contents at that commit**\n- Currently, it's running `git diff sha^..sha` which shows **changes made in that commit**\n- To show the actual **file contents**, it should run `git show sha:file` instead\n\nThe flow shows that when users click on a commit history item in the accordion, they likely expect to see the file contents at that specific commit, but the implementation is showing the diff of that commit instead.\n\n### File Paths (Absolute):\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Template with accordion rendering and toggleDiff function\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Backend API handlers (handleAPIProjectInfo and handleAPIPromptDiff)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb8048ca2fc2fe99 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31982\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 41287</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04c57cbe-a919-4819-8178-dae3046f6f43","uuid":"d9e6cb9b-94b1-49e4-b262-1b3437861db0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the code responsible for the Web UI project detail page, specifically the accordion dropdowns for prompt files. I need to understand:\n1. Where prompt file contents are loaded/displayed in the web UI\n2. Where git log data might be incorrectly used instead of file contents\n3. The relevant handler/template/API code\n\nSearch for things like \"prompt\", \"accordion\", \"project detail\", \"prompt file\" in the web UI code. Look in directories like internal/adapters/web, internal/adapters/http, cmd/cloched, or similar web-related paths. Also search for any templates (.html, .tmpl) files.","agentId":"adb8048ca2fc2fe99","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document with all the file paths and key findings:\n\n## Summary: Web UI Project Detail Page - Prompt File Accordion Code\n\nI've found all the code responsible for the Web UI project detail page's accordion dropdowns for prompt files. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### Key Files and Components:\n\n**1. Frontend Template (HTML + JavaScript)**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**2. Backend Handler**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### Code Flow:\n\n#### Frontend (Template - Lines 53-94):\n\n1. **API Call to Load Prompt Files** (lines 44-76)\n   - JavaScript function `loadProjectInfo()` fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info`\n   - Receives JSON with `prompt_files` array containing:\n     - `path`: file path (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/implement.md`)\n     - `history`: array of commit entries with `sha`, `date`, `message`\n   - Renders `<details>` accordions for each prompt file\n   - Lists each commit history entry as clickable items (lines 59-65)\n\n2. **Display File Contents on Click** (lines 78-94)\n   - Function `toggleDiff(el)` handles accordion item clicks\n   - Currently fetches `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file={file}&sha={sha}`\n   - Displays result in a `<pre>` block labeled `diff-block`\n\n#### Backend (Handler - Lines 978-1095):\n\n**Handler Registration** (Line 136):\n```\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff\", h.handleAPIPromptDiff)\n```\n\n**1. `handleAPIProjectInfo()` (Lines 978-1064)**\n   - Loads prompt files from `.cloche/prompts/` directory\n   - Runs `git log --follow --format=%H %aI %s` for each file (line 1028)\n   - Extracts: SHA, date, and commit message\n   - Returns JSON with `prompt_files` array to frontend\n\n**2. `handleAPIPromptDiff()` (Lines 1066-1095)**\n   - **ISSUE**: Named \"PromptDiff\" but this is where file contents are displayed\n   - Receives `file` and `sha` query parameters\n   - Runs `git diff sha^..sha -- file` (line 1086)\n   - Returns the git diff output as text/plain\n\n### Potential Issue Location:\n\nThe problem appears to be in the **endpoint behavior**:\n- The endpoint is called `prompt-diff` but in the UX it displays what should be the **file contents at that commit**\n- Currently, it's running `git diff sha^..sha` which shows **changes made in that commit**\n- To show the actual **file contents**, it should run `git show sha:file` instead\n\nThe flow shows that when users click on a commit history item in the accordion, they likely expect to see the file contents at that specific commit, but the implementation is showing the diff of that commit instead.\n\n### File Paths (Absolute):\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Template with accordion rendering and toggleDiff function\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Backend API handlers (handleAPIProjectInfo and handleAPIPromptDiff)"}],"totalDurationMs":41287,"totalTokens":31982,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":897,"cache_read_input_tokens":30263,"output_tokens":819,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":897},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
